**Hypothesis testing**
- popularized in ==early 20th century== ([[Topics/Mathematics/People/Karl Pearson|Karl Pearson]], Gosset, [[Topics/Mathematics/People/Ronald Fisher|Fisher]], Neyman, ...)
- An essential method in [[Topics/Mathematics/Statistics and probabilities/Statistics/Statistics|statistics]] : it is a statistical inference method, done to confirm (or not) our observation & hypothesis about a population using only sample ("experimental") data
	- within a desired error level : to trust or not your model (=> Is it "statistically significant" of being more extrem than what chance might produce ?)
- $H_0$ : initial claim (prevailing belief / "premise") about the population that we want to test.
	- Mutually exclusive with the alternative hypothesis
- [[Topics/Mathematics/People/Ronald Fisher|Ronald Fisher]] introduced : p-value, hypothesis testing, null hypothesis, ...

### Applications / Goals
- in [[Topics/Machine Learning/Machine Learning|Machine Learning]]
	- used to check representativeness by **comparing two datasets**
	- to **compare** (mean / k-fold cross validation) **performance of ML algorithms**

### p-value
- the [[Topics/Mathematics/Statistics and probabilities/Statistics/p-value|p-value]] is the probability of having unusual/extrem values which may contradict the "null hypothesis" => ?
- 0.05 value is often used

### Other concepts
- [[Topics/Mathematics/Statistics and probabilities/Confidence interval|Confidence interval]]
- [[___INBOX___/__à trier/Central limit theorem|Central limit theorem]]
- **Test statistic** : numerical summary of the dataset
	- [[Topics/Mathematics/Statistics and probabilities/Statistics/t-test|t-test]]
	- [[Topics/Mathematics/Statistics and probabilities/Statistics/z-test|z-test]] (Z-score)
	- [[Topics/Mathematics/Statistics and probabilities/Statistics/Chi-squared test of independence|Chi-squared test of independence]]
	- [[___INBOX___/__à trier/F-test|F-test]] (in ANOVA test ?)
- one-tailed / two-tailed tests
- [[Topics/Mathematics/Statistics and probabilities/Statistics/degree of freedom|degree of freedom]]
